Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.52,0:00:09.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,MAN 1: Copenhagen Suborbitals's goal is to send a person into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.52,0:00:09.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,MAN 1: Copenhagen Suborbitals的目标是将一个人送入太空
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.00,0:00:13.32,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And they are hopefully doing that by the beginning of the 2030s.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.00,0:00:13.32,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且他们有希望在2030年代初做到这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.98,0:00:20.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,When we succeed in sending a person into space
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.98,0:00:20.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当我们成功地将一个人送入太空时
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.79,0:00:27.78,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it would show the world it's possible for regular people to do a very technically challenging task.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.79,0:00:27.78,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它将向世界表明 普通人有可能完成一项非常具有技术挑战性的任务
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.20,0:00:33.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And also we'll have shown that Denmark has become the fourth nation to send a person to space.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.20,0:00:33.60,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且我们也将表明 丹麦已经成为第四个将人送入太空的国家
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.76,0:00:34.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,MAN 2:{\i1}Ignition.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.76,0:00:34.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,男人2：点火
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.92,0:00:37.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,[ENGINES FIRING]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.92,0:00:37.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,[发动机点火]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.04,0:00:45.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,JACOB: I am the chairman of Copenhagen Suborbitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.04,0:00:45.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,JACOB：我是哥本哈根suborbitals的主席
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.00,0:00:51.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,We're in our rocket workshop just four kilometers from Copenhagen center.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.00,0:00:51.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们在离哥本哈根中心仅四公里的火箭车间里
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.88,0:00:56.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,MADS: In my daytime job, I'm a pricing manager at a sanitary company.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.88,0:00:56.96,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,MADS： 白天的工作 我是一家卫生用品公司的价格经理
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.12,0:01:03.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Here, I'm responsible for the design and testing of parachutes used for the space capsule
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.12,0:01:03.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在这里 我负责设计和测试用于太空舱的降落伞
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.88,0:01:07.71,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and the rocket that will bring it to space and safely back again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.88,0:01:07.71,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,以及将其带入太空并安全返回的火箭
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.52,0:01:14.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,We have engineers, we have artists,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.52,0:01:14.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们有工程师 我们有艺术家
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.52,0:01:17.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,we have a kindergarten teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.52,0:01:17.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们还有一位幼儿园老师
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.24,0:01:19.53,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,What brings us together is the passion of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.24,0:01:19.53,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,把我们聚集在一起的是这样一种激情
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.55,0:01:25.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,trying to solve the almost impossible quest of sending a person safely to space.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.55,0:01:25.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,试图解决将人安全送入太空这一几乎不可能完成的任务
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.92,0:01:33.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,BIANCA: I work as a student assistant in the hydraulics department at MAN Energy Solutions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.92,0:01:33.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,BIANCA：我在MAN能源解决方案公司的液压部门担任学生助理
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.89,0:01:35.52,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Here at Copenhagen Suborbitals,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.89,0:01:35.52,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在哥本哈根的suborbitals这里
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.52,0:01:39.66,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I'm looking into the guidance navigation control subsystem of the Spica rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.52,0:01:39.66,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我正在研究Spica火箭的制导导航控制子系统
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.48,0:01:46.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,PETER: In daily work I'm a software engineer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.48,0:01:46.96,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,PETER: 在日常工作中 我是一名软件工程师
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.12,0:01:54.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Here at Copenhagen Suborbitals I work on mainly electronics radio communications to and from the rocket,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.12,0:01:54.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在哥本哈根亚轨道公司 我的工作主要是研究与火箭之间的电子无线电通信
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.45,0:01:57.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and some of the electronics support systems on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.45,0:01:57.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,以及地面上的一些电子支持系统
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.40,0:02:03.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Space ought to be accessible for anyone on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.40,0:02:03.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,地球上的任何人都应该能够进入太空
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.72,0:02:08.05,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Of course, access to space requires a bit of money,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.72,0:02:08.05,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,当然 进入太空需要一定的资金
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.15,0:02:09.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but we're trying to show
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.15,0:02:09.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但我们正试图表明
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.74,0:02:16.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,that we can actually do it on a quite limited budget compared to the big players in the market.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.74,0:02:16.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,与市场上的大公司相比 我们实际上可以在相当有限的预算内做到这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.12,0:02:20.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,MADS: We're crowdfunded.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.12,0:02:20.94,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,MADS 我们是众筹的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.31,0:02:27.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,500-600 people all over the world are donating roughly nine thousand euros per month.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.31,0:02:27.00,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,世界各地的500-600人每月大约捐赠九千欧元
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.88,0:02:33.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Meaning that we have what corresponds to roughly 10% of NASA's budget for coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.88,0:02:33.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这意味着我们有相当于NASA咖啡预算的10%
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.88,0:02:38.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,We have to be very creative with what we do, how we do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.88,0:02:38.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们必须对我们所做的事情 我们如何做 以及我们能买得起的东西有非常大的创意
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.44,0:02:40.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and what we can afford to buy for the rockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.44,0:02:40.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,以及我们能为火箭购买的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.36,0:02:43.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,PETER: In one of the first rockets,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.36,0:02:43.00,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在第一批火箭中 我们对热能的需求非常迫切
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.06,0:02:48.53,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,we had an urgent need for heat, for a large valve, to avoid it from freezing over.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.06,0:02:48.53,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们急需为一个大阀门提供热量 以避免它被冻坏
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.56,0:02:53.07,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So the quick and dirty solution was a hair dryer from a shop in the harbor
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.56,0:02:53.07,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 快速和肮脏的解决方案是一个来自港口商店的吹风机
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.07,0:02:55.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,that we could use to keep that valve heated.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.07,0:02:55.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们可以用它来保持阀门的温度
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.96,0:03:03.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,MADS: One of the first prototypes I had to make for a ballute contained some air vents
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.96,0:03:03.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,MADS 我必须要做的第一个降落伞原型之一包含了一些空气排放口
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.72,0:03:08.12,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and I tried to design them so that they were kept open by something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.72,0:03:08.12,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我试图设计它们 让它们通过某种方式保持开放
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.24,0:03:12.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So in the end I had the idea to use bra underwires.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.24,0:03:12.62,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以最后我想到了使用胸罩的底线
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.08,0:03:16.79,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So basically the first prototype I made was of size 75A.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.08,0:03:16.79,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以基本上我做的第一个原型是75A的尺寸
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.52,0:03:36.43,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,JACOB: Denmark's too small and the population density too high to launch such rockets from land,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.52,0:03:36.43,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,丹麦太小 人口密度太高 无法从陆地上发射这种火箭
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.43,0:03:37.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which everyone else does.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.43,0:03:37.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,其他国家都是这样做的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.88,0:03:45.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, in the middle of the Baltic there's an old naval training area,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.88,0:03:45.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,幸运的是 在波罗的海中间有一个古老的海军训练区
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:51.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which has about 2.5 thousand km of flat, uninhabited water,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:51.64,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它有大约2.5千公里的平坦的无人居住的水域
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.28,0:03:55.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which is a good place to launch from a safety point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.28,0:03:55.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,从安全的角度来看 这是一个发射的好地方
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.44,0:04:01.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,We're standing in front of the Nexo II rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.44,0:04:01.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们正站在Nexo II火箭的前面
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.44,0:04:04.04,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,This is the section where we have the guidance and control computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.44,0:04:04.04,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是我们拥有制导和控制计算机的部分
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.20,0:04:09.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,We have the GPS systems, the power distribution systems and the telemetry systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.20,0:04:09.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们有GPS系统 配电系统和遥测系统
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.83,0:04:12.46,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,This, here, is the fuel tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.83,0:04:12.46,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这个 这里 是燃料箱
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.62,0:04:16.31,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The fuel is an ethanol-water mix.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.62,0:04:16.31,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,燃料是乙醇和水的混合物
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.56,0:04:19.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,We use ethanol not because it's the best rocket fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.56,0:04:19.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们使用乙醇并不是因为它是最好的火箭燃料
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.06,0:04:24.89,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but because it's water soluble and it's not causing environmental problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.06,0:04:24.89,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而是因为它是水溶性的 不会造成环境问题
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.16,0:04:28.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The Nexo class rockets are basically flying laboratories.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.16,0:04:28.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,Nexo级火箭基本上是飞行实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.00,0:04:33.56,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's all a test flight of what we intend to use for the Spica rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.00,0:04:33.56,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这都是我们打算用于Spica火箭的试飞
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.36,0:04:47.20,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,BIANCA: Spica is going to be launched off the rail and then
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.36,0:04:47.20,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,Spica将被从轨道上发射出去 然后
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.36,0:04:53.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,it'll go supersonic and reach a point where it'll have the engine cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.36,0:04:53.00,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它将以超音速飞行 并达到一个点 在那里它的引擎将被切断
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.16,0:04:56.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,At that point, it should go 3600 km/h.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.16,0:04:56.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在这一点上 它应该达到3600公里/小时
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.00,0:05:05.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And the capsule is going to reach an altitude of 100 km above the earth's surface, which is the Kármán line.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.00,0:05:05.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而太空舱将达到距离地球表面100公里的高度 这就是卡曼线
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.60,0:05:11.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Both the rocket and the capsule will be separated from each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.60,0:05:11.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,火箭和太空舱都将彼此分离
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.60,0:05:13.96,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,They'll be recovered by parachutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.60,0:05:13.96,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,他们将通过降落伞回收
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.64,0:05:19.38,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I'd very much love to be the one that goes into Spica
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.64,0:05:19.38,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我非常希望成为进入天顶星的那个人
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.64,0:05:23.58,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and it's also been suggested as a joke in a way
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.64,0:05:23.58,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这也被认为是一个笑话的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.63,0:05:27.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,because I'm the one who wants to work on the guidance navigation control of the rocket,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.63,0:05:27.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因为我是那个想研究火箭的导航控制的人
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.83,0:05:31.82,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I might as well be the person testing it on myself, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.83,0:05:31.82,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我也可以成为在自己身上测试的人 对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.94,0:05:34.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And I would probably fit the requirements as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.94,0:05:34.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且我可能也会符合要求
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.72,0:05:38.00,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So that would be... something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.72,0:05:38.00,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以这将是......的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.52,0:05:42.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,MADS: Why do we do this? We do it because we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.52,0:05:42.08,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,MADS 我们为什么要这样做？我们这样做是因为我们可以
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.24,0:05:47.41,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And we want to be able to solve this gigantic, near impossible thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.24,0:05:47.41,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我们希望能够解决这个巨大的、几乎不可能的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.52,0:05:53.08,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,JACOB: Amateurs having the possibility of launching humans into space
